1781. Sum of Beauty of All Substrings
Problem Statement

Given a string s, the beauty of a substring is defined as the difference between the highest and lowest frequency of characters present in that substring.

Return the sum of beauty values of all possible substrings.

Approach
Iterate through each index i as the starting point of a substring.
Maintain a frequency array freq[26] for lowercase English letters.
Extend the substring one character at a time using index j.
Update the frequency of the newly added character.
For every substring, find:
maxFreq = maximum character frequency
minFreq = minimum non-zero character frequency
Compute beauty as maxFreq - minFreq.
Add the beauty value to the final answer.
Algorithm
Initialize ans = 0.
For each starting index i:
Create a frequency array of size 26.
For each ending index j from i to n-1:
Increment the frequency of s.charAt(j).
Traverse the frequency array to find:
Maximum frequency
Minimum non-zero frequency
Add (maxFreq - minFreq) to ans.
Return ans.
Code Logic
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
Fixes the starting index of the substring.
for (int j = i; j < n; j++)
Expands the substring by moving the ending index.
freq[s.charAt(j) - 'a']++;
Updates the frequency of the current character.
if (freq[k] > 0)
Considers only characters that appear in the substring.
maxFreq = Math.max(maxFreq, freq[k]);
minFreq = Math.min(minFreq, freq[k]);
Finds the maximum and minimum non-zero frequencies.
ans += (maxFreq - minFreq);
Adds the beauty of the current substring to the result.
Example

Input:

s = "aabcb"

Substrings with non-zero beauty:

"aab"   -> 1
"aabc"  -> 1
"aabcb" -> 1
"abcb"  -> 1
"bcb"   -> 1

Total Beauty:

1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 5

Output:

5
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity: O(n² × 26) ≈ O(n²)
Two nested loops generate all substrings.
Frequency array of size 26 is scanned for each substring.
Space Complexity: O(26) ≈ O(1)
Uses a fixed-size frequency array.
Key Learning
Use a frequency array to maintain character counts efficiently while expanding substrings.
Ignore characters with zero frequency when calculating the minimum frequency.
Since the alphabet size is fixed (26), scanning the frequency array is effectively constant time.
